Section 1: Set Up

  • Set up libraries

Different group CV taken from https://github.com/topepo/caret/issues/540

group_cv <- function(x, k = length(unique(x))) {
  dat <- data.frame(index = seq(along = x), group = x)
  groups <- data.frame(group = unique(dat$group))
  group_folds <- createFolds(groups$group, returnTrain = TRUE, k = k)
  group_folds <- lapply(group_folds, function(x, y) y[x,,drop = FALSE], y = groups)
  dat_folds <- lapply(group_folds, function(x, y) merge(x, y), y = dat)
  lapply(dat_folds, function(x) sort(x$index))
}

Section 4. Function to make AR work on subsets of data

makeARStart <- function(data_mod){
  ar <- data_mod %>% dplyr::select(id, year) %>% distinct() %>% 
    arrange(id, year) %>%
    mutate(year1 = c(NA, year[-length(year)]),
           arstart = year - year1 != 1) %>% dplyr::select(-year1)
  
  ar$arstart[1] <- TRUE
  
  data_mod$arstart <- ar$arstart
  rm(ar)
  return(data_mod)
}

pointDist <- function(spdf) {
  
  size <- nrow(spdf)
    dists <- matrix(NA, nrow=size, ncol=size)
    for (i in 1:size) dists[i, ] <- pointDistance(spdf[i,], spdf) *0.001 #distance in km
    dists
}

Section 7. Function to calculate mean RMSE for a gam model for given validation folds

Create function to calcualte the mean rmse for given gam formula and folds

gamMeanErr<- function(folds, formula, name){
  forest[,paste(name,"Err",sep="")] <<- NA
  forest[,paste(name,"Pred",sep="")] <<- NA
  
  rmseBam <- rep(0, k)
  foreach(i=c(1:k)) %do% {
    test  <- forest[-folds[[i]],]
    train <- forest[folds[[i]],]
    
    train <-makeARStart(train)
    ggamma <- log(nrow(train))/2
   
    selectedmod <- bam( formula, 
                     data = train, 
                     discrete=TRUE, 
                     nthreads=8,
                     gamma = ggamma,
                     method="fREML",
                     family = betar,
                     rho=rho,
                     AR.start = arstart )
    
    
    pred <- predict(selectedmod, type="response",newdata=test, discrete=FALSE)
    forest[-folds[[i]],][,paste(name,"Pred",sep="")] <<- pred
    
    err <- rmse(test$nbv_ratio,c(pred))
    paste("prediction RMSE for fold ",i, ":", err)
    rmseBam[i] <- err
    
    
  }
  
  #individual results 
  forest[,paste(name,"Err",sep="")] <<- abs(forest$nbv_ratio - forest[,paste(name,"Pred",sep="")] )
  
  result <- mean(rmseBam)
  paste("RMSE",result )
  
  return(result)
  
  }

Section 8: Create function to find RMSE for RF models with given formula and folds

rfMeanErr<- function(folds, formula, name){
  rmseBam <- rep(0, k)
  forest[,paste(name,"Err",sep="")] <<- NA
  forest[,paste(name,"Pred",sep="")] <<- NA
  
  foreach(i=c(1:k)) %do% {
    test  <- forest[-folds[[i]],]
    train <- forest[folds[[i]],]
    
   
    selectedmod <- randomForest(formula, train, importance=FALSE)
    
    
    pred <- predict(selectedmod, type="response",newdata=test, discrete=FALSE)
    forest[-folds[[i]],][,paste(name,"Pred",sep="")] <<- pred
    err <- rmse(test$nbv_ratio,c(pred))
    paste("prediction RMSE for fold ",i, ":", err)
    rmseBam[i] <- err
    message(paste("fold",i))
    message(paste("err", err))
    message(paste("rmse bam",rmseBam))
    
  }
  
  #individual errors
  forest[,paste(name,"Err",sep="")] <<- abs(forest$nbv_ratio -forest[,paste(name,"Pred",sep="")] )
  
  #overall error
  result <- mean(rmseBam)
  message(paste("RMSE",result ))
  
  return(result)
  }

Section 14: Create graphs of error by year

Create plots to show error comparison

errorPlots <- function(gamName, rfName, title){
  data <- data.frame(id=forest$id ,year=forest$year,
                     gamerr=forest[,paste(gamName,"Err",sep="")],
                     rferr=forest[,paste(rfName,"Err",sep="")])
  library(reshape)
  meltData <- melt(data, id.vars =c('id', 'year'))
 
  aggData <- aggregate(value~year+variable, data=meltData, mean)
  aggDataSd <- aggregate(value~year+variable, data=meltData, sd)
  aggData$sd <- aggDataSd$value


  ggplot(aggData, aes(year, value)) + geom_line(aes(colour=variable) )+geom_ribbon(aes(y = value, ymin = value - sd, ymax = value + sd, fill = variable), alpha = .2)+ggtitle(title)+labs(y="Mean Absolute error", x="Year", color="Model")+scale_color_manual(labels = c("GAM Age", "RF Age"), values = c("red", "blue"))+coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, 0.2))+scale_x_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(n = 10)) +
scale_y_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(n = 10))

}
errorPlots("ranGamAge", "ranRfAge", "General cross validation for RF Age and GAM Age models")
